creator: Fehners Software Ltd.
descriptionHtml:
Designed by and for breastfeeding mothers who want to track when and for how long their baby feeds, including a useful reminder for when a feed is due. It even tells you which breast to start on!

Breastfeeding or Bottle feeding and trying to keep track of when baby feeds on bits of scrap paper?

Wearing a hair band on your wrist to try and remember which side to start breastfeeding baby on?

Baby Feed Timer does it all for you!
Tracks breastfeeds, bottle feeds, breast pumps, nappies, sleep, solid food, weight, length, notes and reminders(ideal for recording baby's temperature and medicine given). You can even synchronise the data across Android and iOS devices or give non mobile users access to them by logging in to babyfeedtimer.net

Analysed data ready for you and your midwife shows both daily, weekly and monthly averages.

See baby's day at a glance and spot trends easily with easy to read charts.

Simple, quick and easy to use – a must for night feeds!

Recommended by NHS midwives across the UK. *****

HIGHLIGHTS:
√ Personalise the App to your baby by adding a picture, baby’s name and date of birth. It even tells you how old your baby is in weeks.

√ Use the App for more than one baby. Whether it’s a sibling later on or twins or more with full support for multiple timers!

√ Easy to use one button start/stop timer, especially useful during the night feeds.

√ Log breastfeeds, bottle feeds, breast pumps, nappies, sleep, solid food, weight, length, notes and reminders.

√ Focus on what's important to you by hiding activities that you're not interested in such as breast pumps etc. Also re-arrange their ordering to make the most important ones quick to access.

√ See baby's weight and length plotted against data from the World Health Organisation to see what percentile your baby is in.

√ Ability to automatically synchronise data between Phones including iOS devices. For non mobile users let them log into your account at babyfeedtimer.net to view your most recent logs.

√ Pause button. Ability to pause during a feed.

√ At a glance view of how long since baby last fed, next feed time and which breast to use.

√ Reminder to alert you when next feed is due.

√ Analysis of the data including average times between feeds and feed times for the day, week and month.

√ Easy to read charts displaying analysed data, as well as a timeline view so you can see emerging trends, such as baby feeding at the same time every day. This also helps to show days when baby is acting differently such as more dirty nappies than usual.

√ View how long you have fed your baby for that day. Particularly useful for mothers who are monitoring if baby is feeding enough.

√ Manually add feeds if you miss one as well as edit feeds.

√ Add notes to existing logged feeds such as if baby was sick or fussy during a feed. You can also add a note to the log diary itself, for example the baby's temperature and medicine given. You can even set a reminder and alert for the note.


FURTHER FEATURES:
+ You can swap breasts during a single feed.

+ Ability to specify the minimum time you would like to feed on each breast before swapping.

+ Timer continues to run in the background. So you can make calls, play games, etc and the timer will continue to run.

+ Unlimited diary of logged data.

+ Email your data to your computer.

Designed by and for breastfeeding mothers who want to track when and for how long their baby feeds, including a useful reminder for when a feed is due. It even tells you which breast to start on!

Breastfeeding or Bottle feeding and trying to keep track of when baby feeds on bits of scrap paper?

Wearing a hair band on your wrist to try and remember which side to start breastfeeding baby on?

Baby Feed Timer does it all for you!
Tracks breastfeeds, bottle feeds, breast pumps, nappies, sleep, solid food, weight, length, notes and reminders(ideal for recording baby's temperature and medicine given). You can even synchronise the data across Android and iOS devices or give non mobile users access to them by logging in to babyfeedtimer.net

Analysed data ready for you and your midwife shows both daily, weekly and monthly averages.

See baby's day at a glance and spot trends easily with easy to read charts.

Simple, quick and easy to use – a must for night feeds!

Recommended by NHS midwives across the UK. *****

HIGHLIGHTS:
√ Personalise the App to your baby by adding a picture, baby’s name and date of birth. It even tells you how old your baby is in weeks.

√ Use the App for more than one baby. Whether it’s a sibling later on or twins or more with full support for multiple timers!

√ Easy to use one button start/stop timer, especially useful during the night feeds.

√ Log breastfeeds, bottle feeds, breast pumps, nappies, sleep, solid food, weight, length, medication, temperature, notes and reminders.

√ Focus on what's important to you by hiding activities that you're not interested in such as breast pumps etc. Also re-arrange their ordering to make the most important ones quick to access.

√ See baby's weight and length plotted against data from the World Health Organisation to see what percentile your baby is in.

√ Ability to automatically synchronise data between Phones including iOS devices. For non mobile users let them log into your account at babyfeedtimer.net to view your most recent logs.

√ Pause button. Ability to pause during a feed.

√ At a glance view of how long since baby last fed, next feed time and which breast to use.

√ Reminder to alert you when next feed is due.

√ Analysis of the data including average times between feeds and feed times for the day, week and month.

√ Easy to read charts displaying analysed data, as well as a timeline view so you can see emerging trends, such as baby feeding at the same time every day. This also helps to show days when baby is acting differently such as more dirty nappies than usual.

√ View how long you have fed your baby for that day. Particularly useful for mothers who are monitoring if baby is feeding enough.

√ Manually add feeds if you miss one as well as edit feeds.

√ Add notes to existing logged feeds such as if baby was sick or fussy during a feed. You can also add a note to the log diary itself and set a reminder and alert for the note.


FURTHER FEATURES:
+ You can swap breasts during a single feed.

+ Ability to specify the minimum time you would like to feed on each breast before swapping.

+ Timer continues to run in the background. So you can make calls, play games, etc and the timer will continue to run.

+ Unlimited diary of logged data.

+ Email your data to your computer.


If you have any feedback please send it to feedback@fehnerssoftware.co.uk
